It occupies a planet all it own." Th exhibition, on view through Saturday, December 6, is staged in conjunction with "The Poetics of Cloth: African Textiles / Recent Art" at NYU's Grey Art Gallery and a parallel exhibition titled "The Essential Art of African Textiles: Design Without End" at the Metropolitan Museum of Art . Gallery Viewing Hours are Tuesday 10-7; Wednesday & Thursday 10-6; Friday & Saturday 10-5. It occupies a planet all it own." Th exhibition, on view through Saturday, December 6, is staged in conjunction with "The Poetics of Cloth: African Textiles / Recent Art" at NYU's Grey Art Gallery and a parallel exhibition titled "The Essential Art of African Textiles: Design Without End" at the Metropolitan Museum of Art . Gallery Viewing Hours are Tuesday 10-7; Wednesday & Thursday 10-6; Friday & Saturday 10-5. To read the New York Times review and see a slideshow of images from the exhibition, click here .                                              Workshop      Shrines of Ahl al-Bayt: Architecture, Ritual, Representation, and Education                  By Invitation Only                                    Date                   May 7-8, 2012                                                                    Location           NYUAD Downtown Campus                                                                            Art historians, historians, anthropologists, and film historians examine the meaningful concept of Ahl al-Bayt (Family of the Prophet), with particular focus on their shrine complexes in the Arab World and Iran. This workshop highlights the inclusive pieties historically practiced in these shrines and their continuing significance in the contemporary world by examining the architectural, ritual, iconographic, theological, and educational dimensions of these shrines.
